\n| television         = \n| title              =  <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office= may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as \"Office\" (e.g. public office or appointments) -->\n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             =  <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| mother             =  Irina Abelskaya (presumably)\n| father             =  [[Alexander Lukashenko]]\n| relatives          =  [[Viktor Lukashenko]] (half-brother)<br>[[Dmitry Lukashenko]] (half-brother)\n| family             = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| website            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Nikolai \"Kolya\" Aleksandrovich Lukashenko''' ({{lang-ru|\u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}, {{lang-be|\u041c\u0456\u043a\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u044d\u043d\u043a\u0430}} - '''Mikalay Lukashenka'''; born 31 August 2004) is a [[Belarus]]ian public figure and the third son of [[Alexander Lukashenko]], the [[President of Belarus]].\n\n==Biography==\nLukashenko appeared in public for the first time in 2008.<ref>https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=196101&lang=ru</ref> He has attracted significant media attention as his father Alexander Lukashenko took him to official ceremonies and state visits, including meetings with [[Venezuela]]n president [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]], [[Russia]]'s president [[Dmitry Medvedev]], and [[Pope Benedict XVI]].<ref name=\"telegraph\"/>\n\nThere has been no official commentary regarding the identity of Nikolai's mother. However, according to a wide-spread version, his mother is {{ill|Irina Abelskaya|pl|Iryna Abielska}}, a former personal physician of Alexander Lukashenko.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/apr/06/belarus-nikolai-lukashenko|title=Belarus squirms as son follows in dictator's steps|last=Parfitt|first=Tom|date=6 April 2009|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> At the same time, Alexander Lukashenko remains formally married to his wife [[Galina Lukashenko]], albeit the couple is believed to be separated. Lukashenko has never appeared in public with his wife.\n\nIn 2013, Kolya has attracted further media attention as Alexander Lukashenko stated that he would become a [[President of Belarus]], causing numerous speculations in the press.<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/belarus/11925324/Alexander-Lukashenko-The-leader-who-wants-to-turn-Belarus-into-a-North-Korean-style-dynasty.html|title=Meet the pint-sized dictator: The 11-year-old heir groomed in North Korea-style dynasty for Belarus|last=Oliphant|first=Roland|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://www.the-village.me/village/culture/reaction/274741-vneshnost-koli-lukashenko \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u043b\u044f \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e \u2014 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u0423\u0438\u043b\u044c\u044f\u043c\u00bb: \u0412 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0441\u0435\u0442\u044f\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u0441\u0443\u0436\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0432\u043d\u0435\u0448\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0441\u044b\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438] [\"Kolya Lukashenko is the Belarusian Prince William\" - people in social networks discuss the looks of the son of the President of Belarus] - ''The Village'', 26 April 2019.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://news.tut.by/society/558117.html \u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0448\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0441\u044b\u043d\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u2014 13 \u043b\u0435\u0442. \u041a\u0430\u043a \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0430\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0439] (\"The president's youngest son turns 13. How Nikolay Lukashenko becomes an independent media person\") - [[TUT.by]], 13 August 2017.\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lukashenko, Nikolai}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:2004 births]]\n[[Category:Children of national leaders]]\n[[Category:21st-century Belarusian people]]\n[[Category:Belarusian children]]\n[[Category:Lukashenko family|Nikolai]]\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=December 2017}}\n{{Eastern Slavic name|Aleksandrovich|Lukashenko}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               =  Nikolai Lukashenko\n| image              =  Nikolai Lukashenko 2012.jpg\n| image_upright =\n| image_size         =  \n| alt                = \n| caption            = Nikolai Lukashenko in 2012\n| native_name        = \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e\n| native_name_lang   = ru\n| pronunciation      = \n| birth_date         = {{birth date and age|2004|08|31|df=yes}}\n| birth_place        = [[Minsk]], [[Belarus]]\n| baptised           = \n| death_date         =  <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date) -->\n| death_place        = \n| death_cause        = \n| resting_place      = \n| resting_place_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| burial_place       =  <!-- may be used instead of resting_place and resting_place_coordinates (displays \"Burial place\" as label) -->\n| burial_coordinates =  <!-- {{coord|LAT|LONG|type:landmark|display=inline}} -->\n| monuments          = \n| residence          = \n| nationality        = \n| other_names        = \n| citizenship        = \n| education          = \n| alma_mater         = \n| occupation         = \n| years_active       = \n| era                = \n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| known_for          = \n| style              = \n| home_town          = \n| salary             = \n| net_worth          =  <!-- Net worth should be supported with a citation from a reliable source -->\n| height             =  <!-- \"X cm\", \"X m\"  or \"X ft Y in\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| weight             =  <!-- \"X kg\", \"X lb\" or \"X st Y lb\" plus optional reference (conversions are automatic) -->\n| television         = \n| title              =  <!-- Formal/awarded/job title. The parameter |office= may be used as an alternative when the label is better rendered as \"Office\" (e.g. public office or appointments) -->\n| term               = \n| predecessor        = \n| successor          = \n| party              = \n| movement           = \n| opponents          = \n| boards             = \n| criminal_charge    =  <!-- Criminality parameters should be supported with citations from reliable sources -->\n| criminal_penalty   = \n| criminal_status    = \n| spouse             =  <!-- Use article title or common name -->\n| partner            =  <!-- (unmarried long-term partner) -->\n| children           = \n| mother             =  Irina Abelskaya (presumably)\n| father             =  [[Alexander Lukashenko]]\n| relatives          =  [[Viktor Lukashenko]] (half-brother)<br>[[Dmitry Lukashenko]] (half-brother)\n| family             = \n| callsign           = \n| awards             = \n| website            = \n| signature          = \n| signature_size     = \n| signature_alt      = \n| footnotes          = \n}}\n\n'''Nikolai \"Kolya\" Aleksandrovich Lukashenko''' ({{lang-ru|\u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u0410\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0447 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e}}, {{lang-be|\u041c\u0456\u043a\u0430\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u044d\u043d\u043a\u0430}} - '''Mikalay Lukashenka'''; born 31 August 2004) is a [[Belarus]]ian public figure and the third son of [[Alexander Lukashenko]], the [[President of Belarus]].\n\n==Biography==\nLukashenko appeared in public for the first time in 2008.<ref>https://nn.by/?c=ar&i=196101&lang=ru</ref> He has attracted significant media attention as his father Alexander Lukashenko took him to official ceremonies and state visits, including meetings with [[Venezuela]]n president [[Hugo Ch\u00e1vez]], [[Russia]]'s president [[Dmitry Medvedev]], and [[Pope Benedict XVI]].<ref name=\"telegraph\"/>\n\nThere has been no official commentary regarding the identity of Nikolai's mother. However, according to a wide-spread version, his mother is {{ill|Irina Abelskaya|pl|Iryna Abielska}}, a former personal physician of Alexander Lukashenko.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2009/apr/06/belarus-nikolai-lukashenko|title=Belarus squirms as son follows in dictator's steps|last=Parfitt|first=Tom|date=6 April 2009|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref> At the same time, Alexander Lukashenko remains formally married to his wife [[Galina Lukashenko]], albeit the couple is believed to be separated. Lukashenko has never appeared in public with his wife.\n\nIn 2013, Kolya has attracted further media attention as Alexander Lukashenko stated that he would become a [[President of Belarus]], causing numerous speculations in the press.<ref name=\"telegraph\">{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/belarus/11925324/Alexander-Lukashenko-The-leader-who-wants-to-turn-Belarus-into-a-North-Korean-style-dynasty.html|title=Meet the pint-sized dictator: The 11-year-old heir groomed in North Korea-style dynasty for Belarus|last=Oliphant|first=Roland|work=The Telegraph|accessdate=17 November 2017}}</ref><ref>[https://www.the-village.me/village/culture/reaction/274741-vneshnost-koli-lukashenko \u00ab\u041a\u043e\u043b\u044f \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e \u2014 \u0431\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0439 \u043f\u0440\u0438\u043d\u0446 \u0423\u0438\u043b\u044c\u044f\u043c\u00bb: \u0412 \u0441\u043e\u0446\u0441\u0435\u0442\u044f\u0445 \u043e\u0431\u0441\u0443\u0436\u0434\u0430\u044e\u0442 \u0432\u043d\u0435\u0448\u043d\u043e\u0441\u0442\u044c \u0441\u044b\u043d\u0430 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u0411\u0435\u043b\u0430\u0440\u0443\u0441\u0438] [\"Kolya Lukashenko is the Belarusian Prince William\" - people in social networks discuss the looks of the son of the President of Belarus] - ''The Village'', 26 April 2019.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[https://news.tut.by/society/558117.html \u041c\u043b\u0430\u0434\u0448\u0435\u043c\u0443 \u0441\u044b\u043d\u0443 \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0437\u0438\u0434\u0435\u043d\u0442\u0430 \u2014 13 \u043b\u0435\u0442. \u041a\u0430\u043a \u041d\u0438\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0439 \u041b\u0443\u043a\u0430\u0448\u0435\u043d\u043a\u043e \u0441\u0442\u0430\u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0441\u0430\u043c\u043e\u0441\u0442\u043e\u044f\u0442\u0435\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0439 \u043c\u0435\u0434\u0438\u0430\u043f\u0435\u0440\u0441\u043e\u043d\u043e\u0439] (\"The president's youngest son turns 13. How Nikolay Lukashenko becomes an independent media person\") - [[TUT.by]], 13 August 2017\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Lukashenko, Nikolai}}\