olishgovernment\">Ministry of Foreign Affairs. [http://www.ww2.pl/The,1939,Campaign,22.html The 1939 Campaign] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131211211729/http://www.ww2.pl/The%2C1939%2CCampaign%2C22.html |date=11 December 2013 }} [[Polish Ministry of Foreign Affairs]], 2005.</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"rothwell\">{{Cite book |first=Victor |last=Rothwell |title=Origins of the Second World War |publisher=Manchester University Press |year=2001 |isbn=978-0-7190-5958-2 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JLlaN3e4IcsC&pg=PA92#v=onepage&q&f=false |page= 92 |ref=harv}}</ref>\n}}\n\n== Sources ==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{cite journal |authorlink=Dariusz Baliszewski |last=Baliszewski |first=Dariusz |url= http://www.wprost.pl/ar/?O=68347 |title=Wojna sukces\u00f3w |journal=[[Wprost]] |issue=1141 |date=10 October 2004 |language=Polish |accessdate=24 March 2005 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal|authorlink=Dariusz Baliszewski |last=Baliszewski |first=Dariusz |url=http://www.wprost.pl/ar/?O=66711 |title=Most honoru |journal=[[Wprost]] |issue=1138 |date=19 September 2004 |language=Polish |accessdate=24 March 2005 |ref=harv |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070514184605/http://www.wprost.pl/ar/?O=66711 |archivedate=14 May 2007 |df= }}\n* {{cite book |last=Cooper |first=Matthew |title=The German Army 1939\u20131945: Its Political and Military Failure |publisher=Stein and Day |location=New York |year=1978 |isbn=978-0-8128-2468-1}}\n* {{cite journal |last=Corum |first=James S. |title=The Luftwaffe's Campaigns in Poland and the West 1939\u20131940: A Case Study of handling Innovation in Wartime |journal=Security and Defence Quarterly |date=2013 |issue=1 |pages=158\u2013189 |doi=10.5604/23008741.1191778 |ref=harv|doi-broken-date=2020-04-12 }}\n* {{cite book |authorlink=Marek Jan Chodakiewicz |last=Chodakiewicz |first=Marek Jan |title=Between Nazis and Soviets: Occupation Politics in Poland, 1939\u20131947 |publisher=Lexington Books |year=2004 | isbn=978-0-7391